cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it presents a network static analysis tool. It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it captures network functionality such as encryption and stateful processing. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it presents a language designed for network processing that is symbolic-execution friendly. It could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with analyzing and debugging network systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it presents a new language for network processing.
